label.value: positive regulation of cilium movement

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of cilium movement, the directed, self-propelled movement of a cilium.

definition.value: Note that we deem cilium and microtubule-based flagellum to be equivalent.

label.value: negative regulation of cilium movement

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of cilium movement, the directed, self-propelled movement of a cilium.

definition.value: Note that we deem cilium and microtubule-based flagellum to be equivalent.

label.value: cilium movement involved in otolith formation

value.value: The directed, self-propelled movement of cilia of inner ear epithelial cells, resulting the aggregation of otolith seed particles.

label.value: regulation of cilium beat frequency

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency of cilium movement, the directed, self-propelled movement of a cilium.

definition.value: Note that we deem cilium and microtubule-based flagellum to be equivalent.

label.value: noradrenergic neuron differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an noradrenergic neuron, a neuron that secretes noradrenaline.

label.value: noradrenergic neuron development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a noradrenergic neuron over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label.value: noradrenergic neuron fate commitment

value.value: The process in which the developmental fate of a cell becomes restricted such that it will develop into a noradrenergic neuron.

label.value: brainstem development

value.value: The progression of the brainstem from its formation to the mature structure. The brainstem is the part of the brain that connects the brain with the spinal cord.

label.value: noradrenergic neuron differentiation involved in brainstem development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an noradrenergic neuron that is part of the brainstem.

label.value: noradrenergic neuron fate commitment involved in brainstem development

value.value: The process in which the developmental fate of a cell becomes restricted such that it will develop into a noradrenergic neuron that is part of the brainstem.

label.value: lamellipodium assembly involved in ameboidal cell migration

value.value: Formation of a lamellipodium, a thin sheetlike extension of the surface of a migrating cell that contributes to the directed self propelled movement of a cell.

label.value: lamellipodium assembly involved in mesendodermal cell migration

value.value: Formation of a lamellipodium, a thin sheetlike extension of the surface of a migrating cell that contributes to the directed self-propelled movement of a mesendodermal cell.

label.value: establishment of cell polarity involved in ameboidal cell migration

value.value: The specification and formation of anisotropic intracellular organization that contributes to the self-propelled directed movement of an ameboid cell.

label.value: cell-matrix adhesion involved in ameboidal cell migration

value.value: The binding of a cell to the extracellular matrix that contributes to the directed movement of an ameboid cell.

label.value: cell-cell adhesion involved in ameboidal cell migration

value.value: The attachment of one ameboid cell to another that contributes to the establishment of cell polarity that is part of the directed movement of one of the cells.

label.value: cell-matrix adhesion involved in mesendodermal cell migration

value.value: The binding of a cell to the extracellular matrix that contributes to the directed movement of a mesendodermal cell.

label.value: establishment of cell polarity involved in mesendodermal cell migration

value.value: The specification and formation of anisotropic intracellular organization that contributes to the self-propelled directed movement of a mesendodermal cell.

label.value: cell-cell adhesion involved in mesendodermal cell migration

value.value: The attachment of mesendodermal cells to each other that contributes to the establishment of cell polarity that is part of the directed movement of the cells of the mesendoderm.

label.value: establishment or maintenance of cytoskeleton polarity involved in ameboidal cell migration

value.value: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of polarized cytoskeletal structures that contribute to the cell polarity of a migrating ameboid cell.

label.value: establishment or maintenance of cytoskeleton polarity involved in mesendodermal cell migration

value.value: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of polarized cytoskeletal structures that contribute to the cell polarity of a migrating mesendodermal cell.

label.value: sphingosine-1-phosphate receptor signaling pathway

value.value: A G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by sphingosine-1-phosphate binding to its receptor on the surface of a cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: establishment of cell polarity involved in gastrulation cell migration

value.value: The specification and formation of anisotropic intracellular organization that contributes to the self-propelled directed movement of an ameboid cell taking part in gastrulation.

label.value: establishment or maintenance of cytoskeleton polarity involved in gastrulation

value.value: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of polarized cytoskeletal structures that contribute to the cell polarity of a migrating ameboid cell taking part in gastrulation.

label.value: epithelial cell morphogenesis involved in gastrulation

value.value: The change in form that occurs when an epithelial cell progresses from it initial formation to its mature state, contributing to the process of gastrulation.

label.value: epithelial cell morphogenesis

value.value: The change in form that occurs when an epithelial cell progresses from its initial formation to its mature state.

label.value: apical constriction

value.value: The actin-mediated process that results in the contraction of the apical end of a polarized columnar epithelial cell.

label.value: apical constriction involved in gastrulation

value.value: The actin-mediated process that results in the contraction of the apical end of a polarized columnar epithelial cell, contributing to the process of gastrulation.

label.value: amphid sensory organ development

value.value: The progression of the amphid sensory organ over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Amphid sensory organs are the sensory organs of nematodes.

label.value: neuron differentiation involved in amphid sensory organ development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuron that contributes to the progression of the amphid sensory gland.

label.value: neuron development involved in amphid sensory organ development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a neuron over time, that contributes to the development of the amphid sensory organ.

label.value: retrograde extension

value.value: The progression of a neuronal projection over time by the attachment of a part of the cell to an anchor and the subsequent migration of the cell body away from the anchor point.

label.value: dendrite development by retrograde extension

value.value: The progression of a dendrite over time by the attachment of a part of the neuron to an anchor and the subsequent migration of the cell body away from the anchor point.

label.value: amphid sensory organ dendrite retrograde extension

value.value: The progression of an amphid sensory organ's neuronal dendrite over time by the attachment of a part of the cell to an anchor and the subsequent migration of the cell body away from the anchor point.

label.value: cell adhesion involved in retrograde extension

value.value: The attachment of a cell, either to another cell or to an underlying substrate such as the extracellular matrix that contributes to the process of retrograde extension.

label.value: neuron migration involved in retrograde extension

value.value: The directed, self-propelled movement of a neuron that contributes to the process of retrograde extension.

label.value: cell adhesion involved in dendrite retrograde extension

value.value: The attachment of a cell, either to another cell or to an underlying substrate such as the extracellular matrix that contributes to the process of retrograde extension of a dendrite.

label.value: neuron migration involved in dendrite retrograde extension

value.value: The directed, self-propelled movement of a neuron that contributes to the process of retrograde extension of a dendrite.

label.value: cell adhesion involved in amphid sensory organ dendrite retrograde extension

value.value: The directed, self-propelled movement of a neuron that contributes to the process of retrograde extension of a dendrite in a neuron of the amphid sensory organ.

label.value: neuron migration involved in amphid sensory organ dendrite retrograde extension

value.value: The directed, self-propelled movement of a neuron that contributes to the process of retrograde extension of a dendrite of a neuron in the amphid sensory organ.

label.value: glial cell differentiation involved in amphid sensory organ development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a glial cell of the amphid sensory organ.

label.value: cytoneme morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of a cytoneme are shaped. A cytoneme is a long, thin and polarized actin-based cytoplasmic extension that projects from a cell.

label.value: regulation of COPII vesicle coating

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the addition of COPII proteins and adaptor proteins to ER membranes during the formation of transport vesicles, forming a vesicle coat.

label.value: axis elongation

value.value: The developmental growth that results in the elongation of a line that defines polarity or symmetry in an anatomical structure.

label.value: optic vesicle formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the optic vesicle from the lateral wall of the forebrain. This process begins with the specific processes that contribute to the appearance of the vesicle and ends when the vesicle has evaginated. The optic vesicle is the evagination of neurectoderm that precedes formation of the optic cup.

label.value: optic vesicle morphogenesis

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the formation and shaping of the optic vesicle. This process begins with the specific processes that contribute to the appearance of the vesicle and ends when the vesicle has evaginated. The optic vesicle is the evagination of neurectoderm that precedes formation of the optic cup.

label.value: optic vesicle elongation

value.value: The developmental growth that results in the lengthening of the optic vesicle in the posterior direction.

label.value: retinal pigment epithelium development

value.value: The progression of the retinal pigment epithelium over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The retinal pigment epithelium is the melanin-containing layer of cells between the retina and the choroid that absorbs scattered and reflected light and removes waste products produced by the photoreceptor cells.

label.value: neural retina development

value.value: The progression of the neural retina over time from its initial formation to the mature structure. The neural retina is the part of the retina that contains neurons and photoreceptor cells.

label.value: optic cup formation involved in camera-type eye development

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the optic cup, a two-walled vesicle formed from the optic vesicle.

label.value: optic cup structural organization

value.value: The process that contributes to creating the structural organization of the optic cup. This process pertains to the physical shaping of the rudimentary structure.
